title: Shares of several footwear companies are trading higher amid macro optimism following data from Gilead's remdesivir  in coronavirus patients. A potential treatment candidate has raised hopes of a rebound in economic activity and supply chain stability.
Shares of several retail companies are trading higher, rebounding from earlier weakness. Markets have been volatile amid the coronavirus outbreak which caused many retail stores to close down.
